[No clinical signs nor PM changes are available. These data are
anticipated in relation to any die-off in cattle, anywhere -- to
exclude a zoonotic potential and/or infectious disease potentially
spreading within or beyond the national boundaries.

Such information, preferably immediately after the onset of the
die-off, has become even more essential in view of the world declared
free of rinderpest, with vaccination world-widely banned. Rinderpest
has been retained on OIE list to facilitate early recognition and
reporting in the (unlikely) event of re-emergence. - Mod.AS]

