******
[2]Haryana (Kaithal)
Date: 17 Jul 2011
Source: The Times of India [edited]
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-17/india/29783948_1_buffalo-home-mysterious-disease-village-pond


Mysterious buffaloes deaths in Kaithal district
-----------------------------------------------
A mysterious disease in Khanpur village of Kaithal district led to
the sudden deaths of nearly 25 buffalos in the past 24 hours, plunging
the villagers into mourning.

A team of doctors rushed to the village after reports of the disease,
which is killing one cattle almost every hour, since Friday evening,
but have so far failed to identify the disease or the cause of so many
deaths.

The disease was noticed on Friday [15 Jul 2011] evening when
buffaloes started falling to the ground following which villagers
consulted a veterinary assistant in the village. But even after
treatment there was no improvement and buffalos started dying by late
night on Friday. Villagers informed that the buffalos stopped taking
fodder or hay initially and then laid on the floor. A farmer informed
that he had brought his buffalo home from the village pond along with
many other villagers. The symptoms started soon after returning home.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>



[Further information, preferably including lab results, is required.
A per-acute death of cattle immediately after returning from pasture
is suspected to be related to intoxications. This deserves a
veterinary investigation to identify the causative agent, as well as
to exclude other possible causes, including infectious ones. -
Mod.AS]

